  nano ~/umami/docker-compose.yml

  Replace changeme-replace-with-random-string with the value you just copied. Save, then restart:

  cd ~/umami && docker compose down && docker compose up -d

  That's it — Umami stores the secret in memory at startup, so a restart picks up the new value. Your
  existing login and data are unaffected (the database lives in ./postgres-data which isn't touched by
   a restart).




